placeholder.en: The detection of collagen residues through Raman spectroscopy on folio 31r suggests the application of a protein-based binding medium, commonly used in medieval illuminations. This discovery aligns with the potential use of verdigris (copper acetate), a pigment frequently mixed with such binders to enhance adherence and vibrancy. Supporting this hypothesis, the presence of two characteristic FORS peaks at approximately 570 nm and 610 nm corresponds to absorption features typically attributed to verdigris...
